<html>
<head>
<title>CiTR Archiver</title>
<h1>CiTR Archiver</h1></head>
</head>
<body>
<hr/>
<p>Archive begins at 2013-05-21 14:08:52<br/>
Coverage may be spotty.</p>
<p>Instructions:</p>
<p>Date/Time format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS</p>
<ol>
<li>Enter Start Date/Time.</li>
<li>Enter End Date/Time.</li>
<li>Click submit.</li>
<li>Save audio file.</li>
</ol>

<p>To use this archive directly, it accepts startTime and endTime as URL-encoded strings:<br/>
http://airtime.citr.ca:8032/py/arch/download?startTime=...&endTime=...<br/><tt>OR</tt><br/>
http://airtime.citr.ca:8032/arch/d/startTime--endTime</p>
<br/>
<% 
if "timeError" in globals():
   print "<b>Error: Time format invalid.</b>"

%>
<form method="GET" action="/py/arch/download">
   Start Time: <input type="text" name="startTime" /><br/>
   End Time: <input type="text" name="endTime" /><br/>
   <input type="submit"/>
</form>
<hr/>
</body>
</html>
